#### Install
```bash
$ [sudo] pip install google-chrome
```

#### Functions
function|`__doc__`
-|-
`google_chrome.activate()`|activate Google Chrome and bring it to front
`google_chrome.close(urls)`|close tabs with url(s)
`google_chrome.kill()`|kill Google Chrome.app process
`google_chrome.open(url)`|open url(s)
`google_chrome.pid()`|return Google Chrome.app pid
`google_chrome.quit()`|quit Google Chrome.app
`google_chrome.refresh(url, activate=True)`|refresh url. return True if url is opened, else False
`google_chrome.tell(code)`|execute applescript `tell application "Google Chrome" ...`
`google_chrome.url()`|return current tab url
`google_chrome.urls()`|return list of tabs urls
`google_chrome.fullscreen.detect()`|return True if fullscreen mode detected, else False
`google_chrome.fullscreen.enter()`|enter fullscreen mode
`google_chrome.fullscreen.exit()`|exit fullscreen mode
`google_chrome.fullscreen.toggle()`|toggle fullscreen mode

#### CLI
usage|`__doc__`
-|-
`python -m google_chrome.close [url ...]`|close url(s)
`python -m google_chrome.kill`|kill Google Chrome.app process
`python -m google_chrome.open url ...`|open url(s)
`python -m google_chrome.quit`|Quit Google Chrome
`python -m google_chrome.refresh [url ...]`|refresh url(s)
`python -m google_chrome.url`|print current url
`python -m google_chrome.urls`|print tabs urls
`python -m google_chrome.fullscreen.detect`|print `true` if fullscreen detected, else `false`
`python -m google_chrome.fullscreen.enter`|enter fullscreen mode
`python -m google_chrome.fullscreen.exit`|exit fullscreen mode

